From 21d3661303d08c95ffd85d1e3fc6731165e1b0a4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mavis <Mavis@local>
Date: Mon, 1 Jun 2026 07:05:49 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add allow command: time-limited usage that auto-blocks

Adds the `freeblock allow <list> <duration>` command, the mirror of
`lock`. While the allowance is running the list is unblocked so the
user can use the apps freely. When the duration elapses, the Worker
transitions the list into a manual block and the apps get killed
within the next tick.

- SDK: BlockList gains AllowanceStart, AllowanceDuration,
  AllowanceEndTime, InAllowancePeriod, AllowanceExpired, and
  AllowanceRemaining. Active now also flips on when an allowance has
  expired.
- CLI: new DurationArgument accepts HH:MM:SS, HH:MM, and shorthand
  like 20m / 1h / 1h20m / 90s. The status command shows the remaining
  allowance time, and block / unblock / lock cancel any pending
  allowance (with a friendly note).
- Daemon: new AllowAsync hub method; BlockAsync, UnblockAsync, and
  LockAsync all clear any pending allowance so state stays
  consistent. Worker's per-second loop now transitions expired
  allowances into ManuallyBlocked = true so the regular `unblock`
  command can clear them afterward.
- Docs: README and TUTORIAL updated with the new feature.
